  "What does the '1.5 x IQR rule' mean?": "",
  "A method for calculating the mean of a data set from its quartile values": "",
  "A method for identifying outliers by checking if a value falls more than 1.5 times the IQR above Q3 or below Q1": "",
  "A formula for computing the standard deviation using the interquartile range": "",
  "A way to find the median by dividing the data set into four equal groups": "",
  "The 1.5 x IQR rule identifies outliers as values below Q1 - 1.5(IQR) or above Q3 + 1.5(IQR), creating 'fences' beyond which values are considered outliers.": "",
  "What does 'resistant' mean when describing a statistic?": "",
  "The statistic increases with every new data point": "",
  "The statistic always equals zero": "",
  "The statistic cannot be calculated": "",
  "The statistic does not change much when outliers are added or removed": "",
  "A resistant statistic is one that is not significantly affected by extreme values or outliers. The median and IQR are resistant; the mean and range are not.": "",
  "What does 'upper fence' mean in the context of outliers?": "",
  "The maximum value in the data set": "",
  "The value Q3 + 1.5 x IQR, above which data points are considered outliers": "",
  "The mean plus the standard deviation": "",
  "The third quartile": "",
