  "80.0; decreased the mean by 1.3 points": "",
  "76.7; decreased the mean by 4.6 points": "",
  "Sum with 35: 78+82+80+85+79+83+81+84+80+35 = 767. Mean = 767/10 = 76.7. The outlier decreased the mean from 81.3 to 76.7, a drop of 4.6 points.": "",
  "A real estate agent listed 8 home prices in a neighborhood (in thousands): $180, $195, $200, $210, $205, $190, $185, $750. A buyer asks for the 'average' home price. Should the agent use the mean or median, and why?": "",
